                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1267,
                                        1310,
                                        2287,
                                        1806
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": ", i.e. we neglect self gravity. These equations are then augmented by a model equation for the evolution of the wave action and its coupling to the background flow, derived following Jacques (1977). We seek trans- sonic solutions of the wind equations, so we place the momentum equation in critical form (Thompson et al. 2001). With these assumptions, the equations of continuity, momentum conservation, entropy "
                                },
